# AI Code Review Assistant

A full-stack web application that automatically reviews source code using static analysis (ESLint) and AI (Groq/Llama) to help developers catch bugs, security issues, code smells, and performance problems before submitting their work.

## Live Demo

- **Frontend:** https://ai-code-review-assistant-weld-theta.vercel.app
- **Backend API:** https://ai-code-review-assistant-eeb4.onrender.com

## Features

- User authentication (signup, login, profile management)
- Code submission via paste or file upload
- Static code analysis (ESLint) — syntax errors, unused variables, style violations
- AI-powered code review — bugs, security issues, performance suggestions, best practices
- Cyclomatic complexity analysis (per-function complexity, lines of code, function/class counts)
- Auto-generated documentation (JSDoc-style comments)
- Review history dashboard with search and language filtering
- Delete reviews/projects

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React (Vite) + Tailwind CSS |
| Backend | Node.js + Express |
| Database | PostgreSQL |
| Authentication | JWT + bcrypt |
| AI Integration | Groq API (Llama 3.3 70B) |
| Static Analysis | ESLint |
| Complexity Analysis | Acorn (AST parser) |
| File Upload | Multer |
| Deployment | Vercel (frontend) + Render (backend + database) |

## Project Structure

ai-code-review-assistant/
├── client/          React frontend
│   └── src/
│       ├── pages/       Login, Signup, Dashboard, NewReview, Results, Profile
│       ├── components/  Sidebar, Spinner, Toast, ProtectedRoute
│       ├── layouts/     AppLayout
│       └── api/         Axios instance
└── server/          Express backend
├── controllers/     Auth, Project, Review logic
├── routes/          API route definitions
├── services/        Static analysis, AI review, complexity analysis, doc generation
├── middleware/       Auth middleware, file upload
└── db/              PostgreSQL connection


## Database Schema

- **users** — id, name, email, password, created_at
- **projects** — id, user_id, project_name, language, source_code, file_name, documentation, created_at
- **reviews** — id, project_id, review_type, overall_score, summary, complexity_metrics, created_at
- **review_findings** — id, review_id, severity, issue, explanation, suggested_fix, file_name, line_number

## Local Setup

### Prerequisites
- Node.js
- PostgreSQL

### Backend

```bash
cd server
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file in `server/`:

PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/code_review_db
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173

Run the schema in your PostgreSQL database (see `Database Schema` above for tables), then:

```bash
npm run dev
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd client
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file in `client/`:

```bash
npm run dev
```

## How It Works

1. User submits code by pasting it or uploading a file.
2. The backend runs **static analysis** (ESLint) to catch syntax and style issues.
3. The same code is sent to an **AI model** (via Groq) for a deeper review — bugs, security, performance, and design feedback.
4. **Complexity metrics** are calculated by parsing the code into an AST and counting decision points per function.
5. All findings are combined into a single review with an overall score, stored in the database, and displayed on a dashboard.
6. Users can also generate AI-written documentation for their code on demand.

